📘 LVTI (var) – OCP Summary
Rule / Usage	                        Allowed?	        Notes
var x = 5;	                            ✅	                Type is int
var list = new ArrayList<String>();	    ✅	                Type is ArrayList<String>
var x;	                                ❌	                You must provide an initializer
var x = null;	                        ❌	                Cannot infer type from null
var[] arr = {1,2,3};	                ❌	                Array type must be declared explicitly
var in lambda parameters	            ✅ (Java 11)	    Must be used consistently for all parameters
Method parameters / return types	    ❌	                var is only for local variables